{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, abusing their position as an accountant. White-collar crimes of this nature require a penalty that reflects the severity of the theft and serves as a deterrent. However, there are significant mitigating factors in this case: the defendant has no prior criminal record, and they have already made partial restitution of the stolen funds. Balancing the need for punishment and deterrence with the defendant's lack of criminal history and demonstrated willingness to repay the debt, a short term of incarceration is appropriate. This will be followed by a probationary period to ensure the remainder of the restitution is fully paid.",
  "verdict": 6
}
